sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as ML Inference Client
    participant OnlineSvc as feast-online Service<br/>6566/TCP or 6567/TCP (TLS)
    participant FeatureServer as Feature Server Pod<br/>(Python + Go)
    participant OnlineStore as Online Store Backend<br/>(Redis 6379 / PostgreSQL 5432 / DynamoDB 443)
    participant RegistrySvc as feast-registry Service<br/>6570/TCP gRPC or 6571/TCP (TLS)
    participant CronJob as Materialization CronJob
    participant OfflineStore as Offline Store Backend<br/>(BigQuery / Snowflake 443)
    participant Operator as feast-operator
    participant RegistryREST as Registry REST API<br/>6572/TCP or 6573/TCP (TLS)
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS

    Note over Client,OnlineStore: Flow 1: Online Feature Retrieval
    Client->>OnlineSvc: POST /get-online-features<br/>Auth: OIDC/K8s token/None
    OnlineSvc->>FeatureServer: Forward request
    FeatureServer->>OnlineStore: Read features<br/>Backend-specific protocol + auth
    OnlineStore-->>FeatureServer: Feature values
    FeatureServer-->>OnlineSvc: Response
    OnlineSvc-->>Client: JSON/gRPC Response

    Note over CronJob,OnlineStore: Flow 2: Feature Materialization (CronJob)
    CronJob->>RegistrySvc: Fetch feature definitions<br/>gRPC, SA token auth
    RegistrySvc-->>CronJob: Feature metadata
    CronJob->>OfflineStore: Read historical features<br/>HTTPS/TLS, backend credentials
    OfflineStore-->>CronJob: Feature data
    CronJob->>OnlineStore: Write to online store<br/>Backend-specific, backend credentials

    Note over Operator,K8sAPI: Flow 3: Operator Auto-Access RBAC Sync
    Operator->>RegistryREST: GET /api/v1/permissions<br/>Bearer JWT (intra-communication)
    RegistryREST-->>Operator: Permission policies
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create/update RBAC resources<br/>HTTPS/TLS, SA token
    K8sAPI-->>Operator: Confirmation

    Note over Operator,K8sAPI: Flow 4: Notebook Integration (ODH)
    K8sAPI-->>Operator: Watch event: Notebook created<br/>(kubeflow.org/v1 with feast label)
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Read FeatureStore ConfigMaps<br/>HTTPS/TLS, SA token
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create/update notebook ConfigMap<br/>with feature_store.yaml
